                    <li>More consistent theming</li>
                    <li>Bugfix: the delete shortcut was unresponsible</li>
                    <li>Bugfix: screenshot not showing</li>
                </ul>
            </description>
        </release>
        <release version="2.1.0" date="2025-03-01">
            <description>
                <p>2.1.0 Fresh out of the laundry!</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Includes a per-note zoom! So you can get bigger or smaller text</li>
                    <li>Latest set zoom, aka what is most comfortable to you, stays as default for new notes</li>
                    <li>Better readability (WCAG AA or AAA depending on theme)</li>
                    <li>Also slightly better looking theme. Yes even more :)</li>
                    <li>Improved translations</li>
                    <li>Better shortcut and tooltips</li>
                    <li>Fixed a bug where Jorts stayed on light system theme</li>
                </ul>
            </description>
        </release>
        <release version="2.0.1" date="2025-02-25">
            <description>
                <p>2.0.1 Appcenter release</p>
            </description>
        </release>
        <release version="2.0.0" date="2025-02-25">
            <description>
                <p>2.0.0 Release: Slate And Bubblegum</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Revival of an ancient but well loved version of Notejot</li>
                    <li>The app is now named Jorts. You however cannot wear it</li>
                    <li>10 lovely little colours</li>
                    <li>Built atop of modern Linux technologies and packaging formats</li>
                    <li>Smooth transition when changing theme</li>
                    <li>New stickies have a random fun little title and colour</li>
                    <li>A few initial translations included, and more to come</li>
                    <li>Email and links are clickable! Ctrl+Click to open in mail or browser</li>
                    <li>Text supports undo, redo, and you can use emojis :)</li>
                </ul>
            </description>
        </release>
